              So I have the older version of one of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Brita-35530-Ultramax-Dispenser/product-reviews/B00009LHZH?pageNumber=13" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">these</a>.  Today (after taking a nice big swig of water, of course) I noticed that it's all moldy in the filtered water area.  For the life of me, I can't seem to figure out how to get the white middle piece out so I can get to the lower area to clean it.<br /><br />Any suggestions?

              

              
              
